===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''spenden'' from {{etyl|ang}} *{{term||-spendan}} (attested in compounds, as in ''[[aspendan#Old English|āspendan]] "to spend", [[forspendan#Old English|forspendan]]'' "to use up, consume") from a common {{etyl|gem}} word assumed to have been borrowed from {{etyl|la}} ''[[expendere#Latin|expendere]]'' "to weigh out". Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} ''[[spendōn]]'' "to expend" ({{etyl|de|-}} ''[[spenden#German|spenden]]'' "to donate"), {{etyl|dum|-}} ''[[spenden#Middle Dutch|spenden]]'', {{etyl|non|-}} ''[[spenna#Old Norse|spenna]]''

